			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">it is kind of annoying when an attacker twice your power just sends in a single cruiser or something to see what fleets you have, then sends in a huge amount of ships that are almost impossible to defend against. It kind of simplifies the tactics used by the attacker, and the defender often has very little chance of winning because of this simple cruiser.
<br />

<br />
My suggestion would be that battle reports should not be sent to attackers for, say, an hour or two. This way it takes away the advantage the attacker has and gives the defender an opportunity to quickly change tactics before they are attacked, but still allows attackers to see what they will be up against...they just have to wait a bit.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
