			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Alot of people are against slowing down the game, but I agree with your logic.
<br />

<br />
Although I see it like this:
<br />

<br />
Battles and consequently reports should happen at the 1/2 way point (roughly 10 mins) between fleet returns. Takes time to return, should take time to get there.
<br />

<br />
Non personal reports for non-exiles (based on empire relation):
<br />
Council Reports: should show up after 1/2 an hour (noble) ~ an hour(other).
<br />
Related Council Reports (War/Ally): should show up after one (if you are a noble) or up to three hours (ignored or worse).
<br />
Unrelated Councils/Players that aren't Exiles: 8 (noble) to 24 hours
<br />
Unrelated Exiled Councils/Players: 24(noble) to 48 hours
<br />

<br />
Non personal reports for exiles (based on spy rating):
<br />
Council: 1hr 30 min - spy*10min (min 30 mins)
<br />
Related Reports: 4hr -spy*10min (min 1 hour 30 mins)
<br />
Unrelated Councils/Players: 48 - spy*2 (min 24) hours</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
