			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I just think something should be done to make it so that the attacker has to use a bit more strategy and tactics rather than just using a simple tactic like sending in a cruiser...thus giving the defender no chance at all rather than at least some chance. It is possible to beat off someone twice your power, especially if they dont know what to expect when they attack you.
<br />

<br />
Here's another suggestion that may or may not work. What if you send in a fleet of, say, fewer than 100 ships and then lose. No battle report would then be sent back to you. You actually have to send in a sizeable force if you want to see what your opponent has.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
