				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Okay...Elodea, that tactic is great but very unrealistic.  Few people have the patience and time to do something like this.  And what will you do when you inevitably HAVE to leave?  You stop the silly "swapper" defense, as I'll call it, and your attacker will get the best of you, no doubt.  Timing it right would also be a great challenge, because you don't know when your attacker will send his full armada.  Plus I usually scout 2-3 times to make sure enemy fleets have been stationed, which, in my opinion, is a far more feasible cheap tactic for a defender to use than the aformentioned "swapper."
<br />

<br />
Having time limits for BRs would indeed be a major pain in the ass, but it would certainly give the defender a better chance.  I mean few races have the power to win defensive battles against any attacker.  Nowadays, you can get around a full formation with a full armada of flankers and a cloaked cruiser capital on penetrate.  There's really very little chance for the defender.  Also, in this guy's case, there's even LESS of a chance, because he's an underdog.  If a time limit were implicated, it would give the low power player a chance to station fleets or make a "swapper" strategy or escape from his council or call in allies etc etc.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://static.flickr.com/21/38719780_f77a6ed982_o.jpg" border="0" />
<br />

