			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This would pretty much make the game lamespace.  There is already uncertainty after you probe, unless you do some crazy multi-pronged probe, or the fool only uses one type of ship to defend.  People defend with multiple designs (well, anyone half-decent anyway), and you simply are not going to know what all of those are unless you spend an extensive amount of time trying to figure them out.  Delaying this report would just make the game unplayable for the majority of people.  How many people can wait that long after a probe?  Especially the people who can only play for a few minutes at a time, at lunch or whatever.  The cooldowns are more than enough of a heads up for people, and they already annoy me.  I know people who have quit over the cooldowns, and who many more who would quit if this type of thing were implemented.<br />_________________<br />Death to the unbelievers, and some such stuff.
<br />

<br />
Proud member of WD and WD-Maddogs, MK, CN, NC, and whatever you like to call me now.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
